eya_def_tools.data_models.dataset.Dataset
Collection of labelled data for one specific quantity.
The data is labelled by specifying dimensions and including coordinates along the dimensions for each data value.
Attributes: label (Optional[str]): Optional label of the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. assessment_period (Optional[AssessmentPeriod(StrEnum)]): Optional period of or in time that has been assessed and for which the dataset is applicable. This field is to be included only when relevant. Default is None. dimensions (Optional[list[DatasetDimension(StrEnum)]]): Dimensions along which the dataset is binned. All statistics within the same dataset object must have the same dimensions. The dimensions must correspond to and be listed in the same order as the coordinates for the values of all statistics. A dataset without dimensions can only have a single value for each statistic. Default is None. statistics (list[DatasetStatistic]): List of dataset statistic objects that each include data values for a specific statistic type. For example, there may be two statistics, one for mean values and one for standard deviation values.

eya_def_tools.data_models.dataset.DatasetStatistic
Dataset values for one specific statistic type.
Attributes: description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the dataset statistic, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the dataset statistic, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. statistic_type (UnionType[BasicStatisticType(StrEnum), ExceedanceLevelStatisticType]): Type of statistic that the component of the dataset contains. All values must correspond to this statistic. values (Union[float, list[tuple[list[Union[int, float, str]], float]]]): Dataset value(s) as a single number or one or more values at coordinates. If more than one value is included the values must be represented together with coordinates. A single value can be included either with or without coordinates. The coordinates must correspond to and be listed the same order as the dimensions specified for the dataset.

eya_def_tools.data_models.dataset.ExceedanceLevelStatisticType
Probability of exceedance level statistic type.
Attributes: exceedance_level (float): The dimensionless probability of exceedance level (i.e. probability value between 0.0 and 1.0) of the statistic.

eya_def_tools.data_models.eya_def.EyaDefDocument
IEC 61400-15-2 EYA DEF top-level data model.
Attributes: uri (Optional[Url]): Optional URI of the EYA DEF JSON document, which should have the field name '$id' in the JSON document. Default is None. schema_uri (Url): URI of the EYA DEF JSON Schema, which should have the field name '$schema' in the JSON document. It is assumed to be the latest published version if not included. Default is https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IEC-61400-15/eya_def/blob/main/iec_61400-15-2_eya_def.schema.json. uuid (Optional[UUID]): Optional UUID of the EYA DEF document. Default is None. title (str): Title of the energy yield assessment (EYA) report. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the energy yield assessment (EYA) report, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the energy yield assessment (EYA) report, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. project_name (str): Name of the project under assessment. project_country (Alpha2CountryCode(StrEnum)): The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 two-letter code of the country where the project under assessment is located. document_id (Optional[str]): Optional ID of the report document; not including the version when 'document_version' is used. This will typically follow the convention of the document management system of the issuing organisation(s). The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. document_version (Optional[str]): Optional version of the report document, also known as revision. As with the 'document_id', this will typically follow the document versioning convention of the document management system of the issuing organisation(s). The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. issue_date (date): Report issue date in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. contributors (list[ReportContributor]): List of report contributors (e.g. author and verifier) issuing_organisations (list[Organisation]): The organisation(s) issuing the report (e.g. consultant). receiving_organisations (Optional[list[Organisation]]): Optional specification of organisation(s) receiving the report (e.g. client), if relevant. Default is None. contract_reference (Optional[str]): Optional reference to contract between the issuing and receiving organisations that governs the energy yield assessment (EYA) report document, if relevant. The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. confidentiality_classification (Optional[str]): Optional confidentiality classification of the report document, if relevant. The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. epsg_srid (int): EPSG Spatial Reference System Identifier (SRID) for the Coordinate Reference System (CRS) used for all spatial data (e.g. turbine locations) in the EYA DEF document. All location coordinates must be reported in this one CRS, which must have an EPSG code. If different CRSs are used, the data must be converted to be consistent with the EPSG code specified here. utc_offset (float): The offset in hours of the local time zone used for the EYA relative to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). It is applied to UTC time to convert it to local time, hence positive for time zones ahead of UTC and negative for time zones behind UTC (e.g. -6.0 for MST and 9.5 for ACST). All data where the time zone is relevant (e.g. hourly time series and diurnal profiles) must be consistent with this one UTC offset. wind_farms (list[WindFarmConfiguration]): List of all wind farms considered in the EYA. This should comprise internal, external and future wind farms, including those used as reference wind farms in the wind resource assessment, if any. If different configurations are assessed for one or more internal and/or future wind farms in different scenarios, a wind farm object must be completed for each unique configuration, with the relevant configurations for each scenario referenced by wind farm ID. measurement_stations (Annotated[Optional[list[dict[str, Any]]], IEATask43WraDataModel]): List of measurement station metadata documents according to the IEA Wind Task 43 WRA Data Model, including all measurement stations relevant to the EYA, if any. It is recommended that one metadata document be completed for each measurement station, although the WRA Data Model allows for grouping multiple measurement stations into a single document. Default is None. reference_wind_farms (Optional[list[ReferenceWindFarm]]): List of metadata documents for the reference operational wind farms relevant to the EYA, if any. One metadata document shall be completed for each relevant reference operational wind farm. Default is None. reference_meteorological_datasets (Optional[list[Union[ReferenceMeteorologicalDataset, Annotated[list[dict[str, Any]], IEATask43WraDataModel]]]]): List of metadata documents for reference meteorological datasets used in the long-term prediction process of the EYA, which may include details of for example ground-based meteorological stations, reanalysis datasets and mesoscale model datasets used as long-termreferences. Default is None. wind_resource_assessments (list[WindResourceAssessment]): List of wind resource assessments, including results, at the measurement station locations. turbine_models (Annotated[Optional[list[dict[str, Any]]], IEC61400x16PowerCurveDataModel]): List of wind turbine model specifications. Default is None. scenarios (list[Scenario]): List of energy yield assessment scenarios.

eya_def_tools.data_models.general.Organisation

Default is None. contact_name (Optional[str]): Name(s) of contact person(s) in the organisation. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_met_data.ReferenceMeteorologicalDataset
Metadata for a reference meteorological dataset.
The schema describes a dataset at a single horizontal spatial location. Separate data model instances need to be used to describe data at different location from the same source dataset (e.g. different grid cells from a reanalysis dataset).
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID for the reference meteorological dataset within the EYA DEF document. description (str): Description of the meteorological dataset. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the meteorological dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. locations (list[Location]): The horizontal spatial location(s) of the meteorological data. Where a large number of locations have been used and it is not practical to include all, a subset can be included here and elaborated upon in the comments. time_resolution (TimeResolution): Time resolution of the reference meteorological data. data_period_start_date (date): Start of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. data_period_end_date (date): End of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarm
Reference wind farm.
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID for the reference wind farm within the EYA DEF document. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the reference wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the reference wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. wind_farm_id (str): The ID of the wind farm in the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document, containing the configuration data for the reference wind farm. datasets (list[ReferenceWindFarmDataset]): List of metadata documents describing the operational datasets from the reference wind farm that were used in the EYA.

eya_def_tools.data_models.scenario.Scenario
Single unique energy yield assessment scenario.
Attributes: id (Optional[str]): Optional unique identifier of the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. label (str): Label of the scenario. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. is_main_scenario (Optional[bool]): Optional flag to specify whether or not it is the main scenario in the report. Default is None. operational_lifetime_length_years (float): Number of years of project operational lifetime. wind_farm_ids (list[str]): List of the IDs for all wind farms included in the scenario. Each ID refers to a wind farm configuration data object within the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document. Only wind farms for which turbine interaction effects are modelled shall be included. turbine_wind_resource_assessment (TurbineWindResourceAssessment): Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations. energy_assessment (EnergyAssessment): Energy assessment details and results, including gross energy, plant performance, net energy and uncertainties.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.WindFarmConfiguration
A collection of wind turbines considered as one unit (plant).
Attributes: id (str): Unique identifier of the wind farm. label (str): Label or name of the wind farm. abbreviation (Optional[str]): Optional abbreviated label of the wind farm. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. turbines (list[TurbineConfiguration]): List of specifications for constituent turbines. relevance (WindFarmRelevance(StrEnum)): The relevance of the wind farm for the assessment ('internal', 'external' or 'future'). operational_lifetime_start_date (date): Operational lifetime start date of the wind farm in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. operational_lifetime_end_date (Optional[date]): Operational lifetime end date of the wind farm in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. Default is None. installed_capacity (float): The maximum production (in MW) of the wind farm under typical conditions. If there are features in place to increase power output beyond the stated nameplate power of the turbines (e.g. so-called power boost solutions), the wind farm installed capacity should correspond to that increased power, insofar as it is reached under typical conditions and not only in rare exceptions. export_capacity (Optional[float]): Optional specification of the maximum permanently transmittable power (in MW) from the wind farm at the grid connection, or equivalent, if known. If not included it shall be assumed that the wind farm can transmit the full produced output. Default is None. restrictions (Optional[list[OperationalRestriction]]): List of operational restrictions at the wind farm level. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.WindResourceAssessment
Wind resource assessment at the measurement location(s).
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID of the wind resource assessment within the EYA DEF document, used to reference it from other parts of the document. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. results (WindResourceResults): Final results of the wind resource assessment at the measurement location(s). Results should generally be included at the primary measurement height and extrapolated to all assessed turbine hub heights at each measurement location, as relevant.

eya_def_tools.data_models.general.TimeResolution
Resolution of time series data.
Attributes: value (float): The value of the time resolution in the specified unit. For example, for 10-minute resolution, the value is '10.0' and the unit is 'minute' unit (TimeMeasurementUnit(StrEnum)): The measurement unit of time in which the time resolution is specified.

eya_def_tools.data_models.spatial.Location
Specification of a horizontal location in space.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarmDataset
Reference wind farm operational dataset.
Attributes: label (Optional[str]): Optional label of the reference wind farm dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. data_supplier_organisation (Organisation): The organisation that supplied the data. data_type (OperationalDataType(StrEnum)): The type of data in the operational data, categorised as 'scada' for data from a Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (SCADA) system, 'metered' for data from a production meter, 'environmental_measurement' for data from an (on-site) environmental measurement station such as a meteorological mast or a remote sensing device (RSD) and 'other' for any other type of unit. data_source_type (OperationalDataSourceType(StrEnum)): The type of the operational data source. Primary data, such as primary SCADA data, comes directly from the source without processing. Report data refers to data extracted from report document, such as monthly operational reports. Other secondary data comprises all other data source categories, such as secondary SCADA data provided in processed (harmonised) form by a data management service provider. used_data_variables (list[ReferenceWindFarmDataVariable]): A list of the types of data variables included in this dataset and used in the assessment. For a large dataset (such as a full wind turbine SCADA dataset) this field should not include all the variables but only the ones that were used in the analysis. time_resolution (TimeResolution): Time resolution of the operational data. data_period_start_date (date): Start of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. data_period_end_date (date): End of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.TurbineWindResourceAssessment
Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations.

This must refer to an ID of a wind resource assessment included at the top level of the EYA DEF. The schema requires that a turbine wind resource assessment is based on only one wind resource assessment. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the turbine wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the turbine wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. wind_spatial_modelling_processes (list[AssessmentProcessDescription]): Wind spatial modelling processes used in the assessment. results (TurbineWindResourceResults): Results of the wind resource assessment at the turbine location(s). wind_uncertainty_assessment (WindUncertaintyAssessment): Wind related uncertainty assessment categories including results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.OperationalRestriction

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.TurbineConfiguration
Specification of all details for a turbine configuration.
Attributes: id (str): Unique identifier of the turbine. label (Optional[str]): Label of the turbine, if different from the 'id'. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the turbine, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the turbine, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. operational_lifetime_end_date (Optional[date]): Optional operational lifetime end date of the individual turbine in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. Default is None. restrictions (Optional[list[OperationalRestriction]]): List of operational restrictions at the turbine level. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.WindResourceResults
Wind resource assessment results at measurement locations.
Attributes: wind_speed (list[Dataset]): Final long-term wind speed estimate(s) at the measurement location(s) in metre per second. The dimensions of the first standard result dataset should be 'measurement_id' and 'height' (in that order). Further results with other dimensions may be included optionally. probability (list[Dataset]): Final long-term probability distribution estimates at the measurement location(s), as dimensionless values. The first standard result dataset should comprise the joint wind speed and direction probability distributions, with the dimensions 'measurement_id', 'height', 'wind_speed' and 'wind_from_direction' (in that order). The wind speed coordinates should be 1.0 metre per second bins centered on whole numbers, with the first bin half the width (i.e. 0.25, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, ...). The wind direction coordinates should be twelve 30.0 degree bins, with the the first bin centered at 0.0. Further results with other dimensions may be included optionally. turbulence_intensity (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term turbulence intensity estimates at the measurement location(s), as dimensionless values. This field is optional since some measurement devices may lack meaningful turbulence measurements, but it should always be included when relevant turbulence data are available. The first standard result dataset should comprise the ambient turbulence intensity as a function of wind speed, with the dimensions 'measurement_id', 'height' and 'wind_speed' (in that order). The wind speed coordinates should be 1.0 metre per second bins centered on whole numbers, with the first bin half the width (i.e. 0.25, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, ...). Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None. wind_shear_exponent (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term power law wind shear exponent estimates at the measurement location(s). This field is optional since some wind measurement stations may only include a single measurement height, but it should always be included when relevant wind shear exponent data are available. The dimension of the first standard result dataset should be 'measurement_id' only. Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None. temperature (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term temperature estimates at the measurement location(s) in degree C. This field is optional since some wind measurement stations may lack measurements of temperature, but it should always be included when relevant temperature data are available. The dimensions of the first standard result dataset should be 'measurement_id' and 'height' (in that order). Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None. air_density (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term air density estimates at the measurement location(s) in kilogram per cubic metre. This field is optional since some wind measurement stations may lack measurements required to derive air density estimates, but it should always be included when relevant air density data are available. The dimensions of the first standard result dataset should be 'measurement_id' and 'height' (in that order). Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceSubcategory
Plant performance loss assessment subcategory.
Attributes: label (PlantPerformanceSubcategoryLabel(StrEnum)): Label of the plant performance loss subcategory. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the plant performance loss subcategory, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the plant performance loss subcategory, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. basis (AssessmentBasis(StrEnum)): Basis of plant performance loss subcategory assessment. The basis describes the level of detail of the calculation or estimate used in the assessment of the subcategory. variability (TimeVariabilityType(StrEnum)): Considered variability in the plant performance loss subcategory. assessment_process_descriptions (Optional[list[AssessmentProcessDescription]]): Optional description of calculation processes used in the assessment of the plant performance loss subcategory. The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. elements (Optional[list[PlantPerformanceSubcategoryElement]]): Optional plant performance loss assessment elements that fall under the subcategory. The element objects include details and results at the element level. A breakdown of plant performance loss subcategories into elements is optional and can be included only for a subset of the subcategories, as relevant. Whereas the categories and subcategories are fixed, the user may freely define element labels. Default is None. results (PlantPerformanceResults): Plant performance assessment subcategory results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceSubcategoryElement
Plant performance loss assessment subcategory element.
Attributes: label (str): Label of the plant performance loss subcategory element. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the plant performance loss subcategory element, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the plant performance loss subcategory element, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. basis (AssessmentBasis(StrEnum)): Basis of plant performance loss subcategory element assessment. The basis describes the level of detail of the calculation or estimate used in the assessment of the element. variability (TimeVariabilityType(StrEnum)): Considered variability in the plant performance loss subcategory element. is_independent (bool): Whether the plant performance loss subcategory element is independent of all other elements. Default is True. assessment_process_descriptions (Optional[list[AssessmentProcessDescription]]): Description of calculation processes used in the assessment of the plant performance loss subcategory element. Default is None. results (PlantPerformanceResults): Plant performance assessment subcategory element results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarmDataVariable
Reference wind farm operational data variable.
Attributes: label (str): Label of the data variable. This is currently free text but should be replaced by a list of enum options. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the data variable, which should not be empty if the field is included. This may include clarification of the point of measurement, where relevant. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the data variable, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. data_level (OperationalDataLevel(StrEnum)): Whether the operational data variable is provided for each individual wind turbine ('turbine_level'), is aggregated at the wind farm level ('wind_farm_level') or corresponds to a different ('other') unit such as an environmental measurement station. statistic_types (Optional[list[BasicStatisticType(StrEnum)]]): Optional list of the types of statistics included for the data variable. raw_data_availability (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Dimensionless raw data availability (also known as data recovery rate) for the variable. More than one dataset may be included if reporting data availability at different time resolutions or at both wind farm and turbine level. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.TurbineWindResourceResults
Wind resource assessment results at turbine locations.
Attributes: wind_speed (list[Dataset]): Final long-term wind speed estimates at the turbine location(s) in metre per second. probability (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term probability distribution estimates at the turbine location(s), such as wind speed probability distributions or joint wind speed and direction frequency distributions, as dimensionless values. Default is None. turbulence_intensity (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term turbulence intensity estimates at the turbine location(s) as dimensionless values. Default is None. wind_shear_exponent (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term power law wind shear exponent estimates at the turbine location(s). Default is None. temperature (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term temperature estimates at the turbine location(s) in degree C. Default is None. air_density (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term air density estimates at the turbine location(s) in kilogram per cubic metre. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintyAssessment
Wind related uncertainty assessment broken into categories.
Attributes: categories (list[WindUncertaintyCategory]): Wind related uncertainty assessment categories including results. results (UncertaintyResults): Overall wind related uncertainty assessment results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.UncertaintyResults
Uncertainty assessment results.
Attributes: relative_wind_speed_uncertainty (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Uncertainty assessment results as dimensionless relative values expressed in terms of wind speed and calculated as the standard deviation of the wind speed uncertainty distribution divided by the mean wind speed. Default is None. relative_energy_uncertainty (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Uncertainty assessment results as dimensionless relative values expressed in terms of AEP (annual energy production) and calculated as the standard deviation of the energy uncertainty distribution divided by the net P50 (50% probability of exceedance level) AEP. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintyCategory
Category of a wind related uncertainty assessment.
Attributes: label (WindUncertaintyCategoryLabel(StrEnum)): Label of the wind related uncertainty assessment category. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind related uncertainty category, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind related uncertainty category, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. subcategories (list[WindUncertaintySubcategory]): Wind related uncertainty assessment subcategories that fall under the category. The subcategory objects include details and results at the subcategory level. results (UncertaintyResults): Wind related uncertainty assessment category results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintySubcategory
Subcategory of a wind related uncertainty assessment.
Attributes: label (WindUncertaintySubcategoryLabel(StrEnum)): Label of the wind related uncertainty subcategory. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind related uncertainty subcategory, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind related uncertainty subcategory, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. elements (Optional[list[WindUncertaintySubcategoryElement]]): Wind related uncertainty assessment elements that fall under the subcategory. The element objects include details and results at the element level. A breakdown of wind related uncertainty subcategories into elements is optional and can be included only for a subset of the subcategories, as relevant. Whereas the categories and subcategories are fixed, the user may freely define element labels. Default is None. results (UncertaintyResults): Wind related uncertainty assessment subcategory results.
